<!-- FAQ Section                            -->
<!-- ======================================== -->
<section class="section faq-section"> <%# Added section-darker %>
    <div class="container">
        <div class="section-header">
            <h2 class="section-title faq-title">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
            <div class="faq-underline" style="height: 3px; width: 70px; background-color: var(--primary-color); margin: -5px auto 40px auto;"></div>
             <p class="section-description">Find answers to common questions about AI automation and working with FND Automations.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-list" style="max-width: 850px; margin: 0 auto;"> <%# Wrapper for items %>

            <!-- FAQ Item 1 -->
            <div class="faq-item">
              <h3 class="faq-question" tabindex="0" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="faq-answer-1">
                  What exactly is AI Automation for a business like mine?
              </h3>
              <div class="faq-answer" id="faq-answer-1" hidden>
                <p>AI Automation uses Artificial Intelligence software to handle tasks usually done by people. For your business, this could mean automating repetitive data entry, answering common customer questions instantly with chatbots, processing invoices automatically, personalizing marketing messages, or analyzing sales data to find trends – freeing up your team for more strategic work.</p>
              </div>
            </div>

            <!-- FAQ Item 2 -->
            <div class="faq-item">
              <h3 class="faq-question" tabindex="0" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="faq-answer-2">
                  How much does implementing AI automation typically cost?
              </h3>
              <div class="faq-answer" id="faq-answer-2" hidden>
                <p>Costs vary widely based on complexity. Simple automations using tools like Make/n8n might start with setup fees in the low thousands or small retainers. Implementing specific AI tools (like advanced chatbots or document processing) often involves monthly subscriptions ($50-$500+) plus integration costs. Custom AI development is more significant. We focus on delivering clear ROI, often seen within 3-9 months.</p>
              </div>
            </div>

            <!-- FAQ Item 3 -->
            <div class="faq-item">
              <h3 class="faq-question" tabindex="0" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="faq-answer-3">
                  Will AI replace my employees?
              </h3>
              <div class="faq-answer" id="faq-answer-3" hidden>
                <p>Our goal is typically *augmentation*, not replacement. AI excels at handling repetitive, data-intensive tasks, freeing up your employees to focus on higher-value activities requiring creativity, critical thinking, complex problem-solving, and human interaction. It often makes existing roles more efficient and strategic, rather than eliminating them.</p>
              </div>
            </div>

             <!-- FAQ Item 4 -->
            <div class="faq-item">
              <h3 class="faq-question" tabindex="0" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="faq-answer-4">
                  How long does it take to implement an automation solution?
              </h3>
              <div class="faq-answer" id="faq-answer-4" hidden>
                <p>Timelines depend on the project scope. Simple process automations (like connecting two apps) can sometimes be done in 1-3 weeks. More complex integrations or AI implementations might take 1-4 months, including discovery, setup, testing, and training. We provide a detailed timeline estimate after our initial consultation.</p>
              </div>
            </div>

             <!-- FAQ Item 5 -->
            <div class="faq-item">
              <h3 class="faq-question" tabindex="0" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="faq-answer-5">
                  What results can I realistically expect from automation?
              </h3>
              <div class="faq-answer" id="faq-answer-5" hidden>
                <p>Results depend on the process automated. Common outcomes include significant time savings on manual tasks (often 50-90% reduction for specific tasks), reduced error rates, faster response times (e.g., for customer service or lead follow-up), improved data accuracy, better resource allocation, and data-driven insights for decision-making, ultimately leading to cost savings or revenue growth.</p>
              </div>
            </div>

            <!-- FAQ Item 6 -->
            <div class="faq-item">
                 <h3 class="faq-question" tabindex="0" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="faq-answer-6">
                     What technologies do you primarily use (e.g., Make, n8n, OpenAI)?
                 </h3>
                 <div class="faq-answer" id="faq-answer-6" hidden>
                     <p>We leverage a range of powerful tools based on client needs. Our core stack often includes leading integration platforms like Make.com and n8n, flexible databases like Airtable, and advanced AI models via APIs from OpenAI (GPT series), Anthropic (Claude), and Google AI. We also integrate with various CRMs, marketing platforms, and other business software.</p>
                 </div>
             </div>

             <!-- FAQ Item 7 -->
            <div class="faq-item">
                 <h3 class="faq-question" tabindex="0" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="faq-answer-7">
                     How do we get started working with FND Automations?
                 </h3>
                 <div class="faq-answer" id="faq-answer-7" hidden>
                     <p>The first step is an initial consultation (usually free). We'll discuss your business challenges, goals, and current processes. Based on this, we can identify potential high-impact automation opportunities and suggest next steps, which might involve a deeper discovery phase or a proposal for a specific project.</p>
                 </div>
             </div>

             <!-- FAQ Item 8 -->
            <div class="faq-item">
                 <h3 class="faq-question" tabindex="0" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="faq-answer-8">
                     Do you offer ongoing support and maintenance?
                 </h3>
                 <div class="faq-answer" id="faq-answer-8" hidden>
                     <p>Yes, absolutely. Automation isn't always "set it and forget it." We offer various support and maintenance packages to ensure your automations continue running smoothly, adapt to software updates from connected apps, and remain optimized as your business evolves.</p>
                 </div>
             </div>

             <!-- FAQ Item 9 -->
            <div class="faq-item">
                  <h3 class="faq-question" tabindex="0" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="faq-answer-9">
                     What kind of access or information do you need from us?
                  </h3>
                  <div class="faq-answer" id="faq-answer-9" hidden>
                      <p>This depends on the project. Typically, we'll need insights into your current workflow, access to relevant software platforms (via secure API keys or dedicated logins), and potentially sample data for testing. We prioritize security and data privacy, using secure methods for credential handling and adhering to strict confidentiality.</p>
                  </div>
              </div>

             <!-- FAQ Item 10 -->
             <div class="faq-item">
                  <h3 class="faq-question" tabindex="0" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="faq-answer-10">
                     Can you automate highly specific or unique processes for my industry?
                  </h3>
                  <div class="faq-answer" id="faq-answer-10" hidden>
                      <p>Yes, that's one of our core strengths. While we use standard tools, we specialize in designing *custom* automation workflows and integrations tailored to your specific business logic and industry requirements. We don't believe in one-size-fits-all solutions.</p>
                  </div>
              </div>

             <!-- Add more relevant FAQs -->

        </div> <!-- /.faq-list -->
    </div> <!-- /.container -->
</section> <!-- /.faq-section -->

